@startuml
title Calculator System — Class Overview (with Error Logging)

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Calculator {
  .. binary operations (arity=2) ..
  + add(a, b)
  + subtract(a, b)
  + multiply(a, b)
  + divide(a, b)
  + power(base, exponent)
  .. unary operations (arity=1) ..
  + factorial(n: int): int
  + square(x)
  + cube(x)
  + sqrt(x)
  + cbrt(x)
  + log10(x)
  + ln(x)
}

note bottom of Calculator
  Stateless — no instance state between calls.
  divide raises ZeroDivisionError; domain ops
  raise ValueError on invalid input.
end note

class OperationRegistry {
  - _calculator: Calculator
  - _operations: dict[str, int]
  - _sorted_names: list[str]
  --
  + __init__(calculator: Calculator)
  + get_operations(): List[str]
  + get_arity(name: str): int
  + call(name: str, *args): Any
}

note right of OperationRegistry
  Uses Python inspect module at construction
  to discover operations and their arity.
  Raises KeyError for unknown operations.
  Forwards Calculator exceptions on call().
end note

class ErrorLogger <<new>> {
  - _log_file: str
  --
  + __init__(log_file: str = "error.log")
  + log_invalid_operation(operation_name, message)
  + log_invalid_operand(operation_name, operand_value, message)
  + log_incorrect_argument_count(operation_name, required, actual, message)
  + log_runtime_calculation_error(operation_name, operands, error_type, message)
  - _timestamp(): str
  - _write(entry: str): None
}

note right of ErrorLogger
  NEW — independent of Calculator and Registry.
  Appends timestamped entries to error.log.
  IOError/PermissionError caught and printed
  to stderr; never raises to caller.
end note

class OperationHistory {
  - _entries: list[str]
  --
  + __init__()
  + record(operation_name: str, operands: tuple, result: Any): None
  + get_entries(): list[str]
  + display(): str
  + write_to_file(filepath: str): None
}

note right of OperationHistory
  Independent — no dependency on Calculator
  or OperationRegistry.
  Entries formatted as: op(args) = result.
  write_to_file() called at all session exit paths.
  IOError on write is silently logged to stderr.
end note

package "cli (module-level functions)" {
  class parse_cli_operand <<function>> {
    parse_cli_operand(operand_str: str): Union[int, float]
  }
  class run_cli <<function>> {
    run_cli(argv: list[str] | None = None): int
  }
}

package "interactive (module-level functions)" {
  class parse_operand <<function>> {
    parse_operand(user_input: str): Union[int, float]
  }
  class display_history_indexed <<function>> {
    display_history_indexed(history: OperationHistory): None
  }
  class run_interactive_session <<function>> {
    run_interactive_session(calculator: Calculator = None): None
  }
}

class "__main__\n(entry point dispatcher)" as Main <<module>> {
  if len(sys.argv) > 1:
    run_cli() → sys.exit(rc)
  else:
    run_interactive_session()
}

OperationRegistry *-- Calculator : composition\n(holds reference)

run_cli --> Calculator : instantiates per invocation
run_cli --> OperationRegistry : instantiates per invocation
run_cli --> ErrorLogger : instantiates per invocation
run_cli --> OperationHistory : instantiates per invocation
run_cli ..> parse_cli_operand : calls for each operand

run_interactive_session --> Calculator : creates if None
run_interactive_session --> OperationRegistry : creates and uses
run_interactive_session --> OperationHistory : creates per session
run_interactive_session --> ErrorLogger : creates per session
run_interactive_session ..> parse_operand : calls for each operand
run_interactive_session ..> display_history_indexed : calls on "h" command

Main --> run_cli : if CLI args present
Main --> run_interactive_session : if no CLI args

@enduml
